{
  "$comment": "Packing suggestions, agreed by both languages. voyalier-core computes them (packing.rs::build_packing_list); mock.ts reimplements the same rules for component tests. `thresholds` is the single declaration of every number the rules turn on — the mock imports it rather than restating it, the way it already imports prompts.json and readiness-links.json, so there is one copy and nothing to keep in sync. voyalier-core's parity_packing_matches_the_contract holds Rust to it; apps/web's parity.test.ts holds the mock. `cases` pins rule output as well, because a thresholds-only golden would not catch a mirror that compared with the wrong operator.",
  "$whyTheseCases": "Hand-designed for the boundaries, which is where a mirror drifts. 'exactly at every threshold' is the load-bearing one: warm layers fire *below* the cold low (strict), every other rule fires *at or above* its number (inclusive), so an operator slip in either language flips exactly one suggestion and this case catches it. 'just under every threshold' is its mirror image. Expected output is generated from the core and reviewed; the core's own unit tests judge whether it is right, this judges whether the mock agrees. Regenerate deliberately, never to turn a red test green.",
  "thresholds": {
    "coldLowC": 5.0,
    "warmHighC": 22.0,
    "wetSharePct": 40.0,
    "highUv": 8.0,
    "poorAqi": 100,
    "laundryNights": 7
  },
